  assign cat_4_nav = 'Hunting'
  assign cat_4_title = 'Hunting With the Vsling®'

  assign p_q1 = 'What is the Vsling® Bow Sling?'
  assign p_a1_plain = 'The Vsling® is a 100% elastic, patent-pending bow sling made in Hector, Minnesota USA. It keeps your compound bow comfortably snug to your body for hands-free carry and stays on the bow during the shot. Unlike traditional slings that hang loose, slap, snag, and must be removed before drawing, the Vsling® lets you transition from carry to full draw in seconds without ever taking it off.'

  assign p_q2 = 'Does the Vsling® get in the way during the shot?'
  assign p_a2_plain = 'No. The design keeps the sling snug to your bow and completely clear of the arrow path during the shot. You draw, aim, and shoot. The Vsling® is not a factor — from a treestand, the ground, or any angle.'

  assign p_q3 = 'Do I need to remove the Vsling® before I shoot?'
  assign p_a3_plain = 'Never. That is the entire point. The Vsling® is designed so you never have to take it off when it is time to shoot — less movement, less noise, no wasted seconds. No interference: stays clear of your sight, rest, and bow string. Always ready: go from carry to full draw instantly. Silent and secure: no clanking buckles or straps when the moment comes.'

  assign p_q4 = 'Is the Vsling® comfortable to wear all day?'
  assign p_a4_plain = 'Yes. The 100% elastic construction keeps your bow comfortably snug without digging in or creating pressure points. Think of it like a baby carrier for your bow — balanced, comfortable, and freeing your hands for glassing, climbing, and calling. Pair it with the Vsling® Bino Sling for the same hands-free carry on your binoculars.'

  assign p_q5 = 'What makes the Vsling® different from a traditional bow sling?'
  assign p_a5_plain = 'Traditional bow slings hang loose, bounce against your body, slap branches, and have to be removed before you shoot. The Vsling® holds your bow tight to your body using 100% elastic material that moves with you silently. No removal before the shot. Transitions from carry to shoot in seconds. See the full comparison at vslingarchery.com/pages/vsling-vs-traditional-bow-sling.'

  assign p_q6 = 'Is the Vsling® patented?'
  assign p_a6_plain = 'Yes, The Vsling® is patent pending.'

  assign p_q7 = 'What colors does the Vsling® come in?'
  assign p_a7_plain = 'The Vsling® Bow Sling is available in Black, Brown, Camouflage, and Red. Contact vslingarchery.com for custom color orders.'

  assign c_q1 = 'What bow models is the Vsling® compatible with?'
  assign c_a1_plain = 'The Vsling® has been tested on Mathews V3 31, Mathews Phase 4, Hoyt RX-7 Ultra, Hoyt Ventum Pro 33, Elite EnKore, Elite Remedy, Prime Nexus 2, Bear Refine EKO, PSE Fortis, Bowtech Revolt X, and Darton Spectra E. It fits most modern compound bows with no extra hardware.'

  assign c_q2 = 'Will the Vsling® fit my gun or crossbow?'
  assign c_a2_plain = 'Yes. The Vsling® will attach to any gun or crossbow with two swivel studs. The Vsling® Crossbow/Gun Edition is built from the same 100% elastic material and ships with two loose key rings for a custom install on any setup.'

  assign c_q3 = 'Will the Vsling® work with a bow-mounted quiver?'
  assign c_a3_plain = 'Yes. The Vsling® sits clear of standard bow-mounted quivers and does not interfere with arrow clearance.'

  assign c_q4 = 'Does Vsling make a bino sling?'
  assign c_a4_plain = 'Yes. The Vsling® Bino Sling uses the same 100% elastic system for hands-free binocular carry — steady, quiet, and comfortable while you glass. Shop it at vslingarchery.com/products/vsling-bino-sling.'

  assign c_q5 = 'Will the Vsling® fit my bow?'
  assign c_a5_plain = 'Yes. The Vsling® is built to be universal. Whether you shoot a flagship compound or a budget-friendly bow, the elastic design adjusts to fit securely. Universal fit works with virtually any compound bow. Easy setup with a snug double knot. Field adjustable in seconds with no tools needed.'

  assign c_q6 = 'Will the Vsling® Bino Sling keep my binoculars tight to my chest without restricting use?'
  assign c_a6_plain = 'Yes. The Vsling® Bino Sling uses 100% elastic tension to keep your optics snug, stable, and quiet against your chest while still allowing full range of motion. You can glass instantly without straps tangling or pulling tight.'

  assign c_q7 = 'Does the Vsling® Bino Sling work with any size binoculars?'
  assign c_a7_plain = 'Absolutely. The design is a universal fit, stretching to any bino size. Whether you are running compact 8x32s, the most common 10x42s, or even big 12x50s, the Vsling® adapts and stays comfortable all day.'

  assign i_q1 = 'How do I install the Vsling® Bow Sling?'
  assign i_a1_plain = "Loop the sling through your bow's existing sling attachment points, run it through itself to create the carry loop, then tie a snug double knot. Adjust until you reach your preferred fit, re-snug the knot, and you are ready to go. Full installation video at @VslingArchery on YouTube. Takes under two minutes."

  assign i_q2 = 'Do I need any tools to install the Vsling®?'
  assign i_a2_plain = 'No tools required. Installs entirely by hand.'

  assign i_q3 = 'How tight should I set the Vsling®?'
  assign i_a3_plain = 'Set the tension so the bow sits snugly against your body during carry — close enough that it does not swing or bounce, but not so tight it digs in. Tie snug — not cranked down — Vsling® elastic does the work.'

  assign i_q4 = 'Why knots, not clips?'
  assign i_a4_plain = '<p>The Vsling® is built with purpose: no clips, no noise, no failure points. Here is why the double knot is the smarter choice for serious hunters.</p><ul><li><strong>Reliable</strong> — Knots do not freeze, squeak, or clap like clips.</li><li><strong>Universal</strong> — Fits every riser and bow cutout perfectly.</li><li><strong>Silent</strong> — Zero rattle, zero metal-on-metal noise.</li><li><strong>Field-proven</strong> — Adjust or re-tie anywhere, anytime.</li></ul><p><strong>Quick tips</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Tie snug</strong> — Not cranked down — Vsling® elastic does the work.</li><li><strong>To loosen</strong> — Work the double knot out gently — do not pick at it.</li><li><strong>Pro hack</strong> — A pair of needle-nose pliers makes loosening an over-tight knot quick and easy. Set it once and forget it — Vsling® stays locked until you want it loose.</li></ul>'

  assign f_q1 = 'Can I use the Vsling® when climbing a treestand?'
  assign f_a1_plain = 'Yes. The Vsling® keeps your bow secure and snug to your body with both hands completely free for climbing. No dangling bow, no extra noise on the way up.'

  assign f_q2 = 'Is the Vsling® good for turkey hunting?'
  assign f_a2_plain = 'Absolutely. The Vsling® stays on for the shot, allowing a smooth silent transition from carry to full draw the instant a bird steps into range — no last-second unclipping or movement.'

  assign f_q3 = 'Is the Vsling® quiet in the field?'
  assign f_a3_plain = 'Yes. The 100% elastic design eliminates the slapping, snagging, and bouncing that makes traditional slings noisy. Set it and forget it.'

  assign f_q4 = 'Does the Vsling® have a warranty?'
  assign f_a4_plain = 'Yes — every Vsling® comes with a 1-year warranty. Email sam@vslingarchery.com if anything is not right.'

  assign f_q5 = 'Will it work with a backpack?'
  assign f_a5_plain = '100% — Vsling® is built to adapt. Backpack, layers, whatever. Carry better. Shoot without removing it.'

